                            <comment id="276767" author="adilger" created="Wed, 5 Aug 2020 21:39:37 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;It would also be useful to print a brief error message and non-zero return code if no argument is given and no Lustre filesystems are mounted on the node, like &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs df: no Lustre filesystems found&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and exit with &quot;&lt;tt&gt;ENOENT = 2&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="216344" author="adilger" created="Thu, 14 Dec 2017 18:47:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&quot;lfs df&quot; should process all of the additional arguments (e.g. &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs df /mnt/lustre /mnt/lustre2&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; should show status for both filesystems).  If an error is hit during argument processing, the first such error should be saved and argument processing should continue, and the error returned at the end.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
